{"_id":"post-a8341768-327a-4c54-ad96-ec431f0206e0","_type":"post","title":"Making Repl Identity More Accessible","slug":{"_type":"slug","current":"repl-identity-via-cli"},"body":[{"_key":"7fd3fa8d4d72","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"In August last year, we announced ","_key":"7fd3fa8d4d720"},{"_type":"span","marks":["41e1b6132b3c"],"text":"Repl Identity","_key":"7fd3fa8d4d721"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":", a signed identity for every Repl that your code can use to authenticate other Repls when communicating with your APIs and services.","_key":"7fd3fa8d4d722"}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"41e1b6132b3c","_type":"link","href":"https://blog.replit.com/repl-identity"}],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"33e2cf3317da","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"For a quick refresher, you can try out the ","_key":"33e2cf3317da0"},{"_type":"span","marks":["61b7f4fb73c9"],"text":"demo","_key":"33e2cf3317da1"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" that decodes the identity token and outputs it to the shell.","_key":"33e2cf3317da2"}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"61b7f4fb73c9","_type":"link","href":"https://replit.com/@mattiselin/repl-identity#main.go"}],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"3a0885f17aec","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"We have a ","_key":"3a0885f17aec0"},{"_type":"span","marks":["7efc6ae23086"],"text":"Go package","_key":"3a0885f17aec1"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" for this already (","_key":"3a0885f17aec2"},{"_type":"span","marks":["89645780ca59"],"text":"docs here","_key":"3a0885f17aec3"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"), but there's a limited selection of bindings for other languages. To that end, we're rolling out a command-line tool in every Repl that allows you to use features like Repl Identity in any language that can run a subprocess.","_key":"3a0885f17aec4"}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"7efc6ae23086","_type":"link","href":"https://github.com/replit/go-replidentity"},{"_key":"89645780ca59","_type":"link","href":"https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/replit/go-replidentity"}],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"f3b9a2834f30","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Here's a quick demo that you can try in our own Repls:","_key":"f3b9a2834f300"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_type":"codeBlock","language":"text","codeContent":"$ TOKEN=$($REPLIT_CLI identity create -audience=\"the target repl id\")\n$ $REPLIT_CLI identity verify -audience=\"the target repl id\" -token=\"${TOKEN}\" -json\n{\n  \"replid\": \"ff2d906a-0a47-482b-9067-1ac0a078c394\",\n  \"user\": \"mattiselin\",\n  \"slug\": \"replit-cli\",\n  \"aud\": \"the target repl id\"\n}\n","_key":"e8354e793b33"},{"_key":"f181defbe14e","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Check out this example ","_key":"f181defbe14e0"},{"_type":"span","marks":["0b41fa7cd147"],"text":"Python Repl","_key":"f181defbe14e1"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" that creates and verifies a Repl Identity token:","_key":"f181defbe14e2"}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"0b41fa7cd147","_type":"link","href":"https://replit.com/@mattiselin/repl-identity-cli#main.py"}],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_type":"embed","_id":"04fb644b-e55d-40fc-9199-113460e330d7","url":"https://replit.com/@mattiselin/repl-identity-cli?embed=true#main.py","_key":"3d927af6198e"},{"_key":"b157c94fd1ba","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"You can wrap this command in your code to do token creation and verification without needing a direct language binding.","_key":"b157c94fd1ba0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"967f6f83347b","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Enjoy!","_key":"967f6f83347b0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"}],"publishedAt":"2023-01-10T22:00:00.000Z"}